message.entry: Input image {0} must be a 2-D grayscale image.
Input image {0} must be a 2-D grayscale image of size at least 3-by-3.
Input mask must be a 2-D matrix with the same size as input image {0}.
Inputs {0} and {1} must be vectors with equal length.

The input mask covers the entire image and contains no boundary pixels. Pixels on the outer boundary of the input mask are used as boundary condition to solve the soap film PDE over the mask pixels. The resulting image will be black. Please check that the input mask does not cover the entire image.
No region to fill. To define a polygon, you must specify 3 or more vertices.
